==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obtend
<hw>Ob*tend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Obtended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Obtending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>obtendere</ets>,
<ets>obtentum</ets>, to stretch or place before or against;
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>tendere</ets> to stretch.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To oppose; to hold out in opposition.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To offer as the reason of anything; to
pretend.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obtenebration</ent>⟦br⟧
